  "core_payload": {
    "content_type": "markdown",
    "content": "# N1Hub Projects\n\n## 1. Dream Direction\nThe Dream branch pushes the portfolio itself toward a cleaner and more intelligible fabric: a visible live core, a strategic halo, and a remembered archive instead of one flat soup of projects.\n\n## 2. Desired Future State\n- a portfolio map that clearly distinguishes current platform work, strategic expansion lines, and archived memory.\n- stronger linkage between project hubs and the capsule-production stack beneath them.\n- cleaner Real/Dream posture for every major initiative.\n- more explicit project-capital paths from active work into templates, marketplace circulation, and institutional memory.\n- better portfolio hygiene so the platform can grow without losing legibility.\n\n## 3. Why It Matters\nDream preserves the idea that projects are not merely records. They are one of the main structural ways N1Hub thinks, plans, executes, archives, and compounds value over time.\n"
  },
  "neuro_concentrate": {
    "summary": "N1Hub Projects in the Dream branch represents a more mature portfolio fabric for project creation, branching, delivery, archive memory, and later circulation. It pushes toward a clearer live core, strategic halo, and remembered archive without breaking lineage. The branch matters because N1Hub is accumulating not only capsules, but whole project lines that need to remain intelligible as one evolving landscape. Dream therefore preserves a stronger project model where execution, portfolio topology, archive memory, and capital formation stay connected from the beginning rather than stitched together later.",
